The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has taken off its campaigns in Lagos, with concerted efforts aimed at reconciling aggrieved parties. Informed sources revealed that top leaders of the party met in Lagos on Friday and came to a reasonable conclusion that the party could only secure Lagos under an umbrella. The special reconciliation committee under the chairmanship of Eyitayo Jegede (SAN) was set up by National Working Committee (NCW) of PDP under the leadership on Dr. Iyorchia Ayu, the National Chairman of PDP.   Four nuggets from George Bernard Shaw     Ndigbo not under attack in Lagos – Ohanaeze leader     The thrilla in Abuja   The source, who craved anonymity owing to the sensitivity of that issue, said, “The process of aligning the various passionate interests in Lagos PDP got-off on a very promising note, with the visit of members of the PDP Special Reconciliation Committee to Lagos State during the week. The common desire by the various interests to see PDP reclaim Lagos; thereby breaking the APC suffocating hold on Lagosians is very re-assuring. From all indications, the resolve is to stop the few profiting from the disunity in Lagos PDP.” The source added, “The process of aligning the various passionate interests in Lagos PDP got-off on a very promising note, with the visit of members of the PDP Special Reconciliation Committee to Lagos State during the week. The common desire by the various interests to see PDP reclaim Lagos thereby breaking the APC suffocating hold on Lagosians is very re-assuring.”a